   <note>This document is a letter dated May 4, 1818, from Tennessee Governor Joseph McMinn to Colonel George Gillespie. Governor McMinn writes this letter in regards to the compensation Gillespie will receive for his work as commissioner for valuing Cherokee improvements. The letter also includes a table of goods received to be distributed amongst the Cherokee.</note>
